<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98935979929737></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98935979929737><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98935979929737>RE: Training Points</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98935979929737#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 8th 6:09 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I am a 33 barb shammy and have not found a guild trainer anywhere else.&nbsp;&nbsp;I hear their might be on in Kunark possibly in FV or OT but have not verified.  But there is nothing under Freeport for sure for you to train in.  You will be KOS in ogre and troll towns so don't bother.  Get the skills you absolutely want to have and then I would just bank my points.  There are not alot of skills available in the teens or twenties.  I would save them for learning a new weapon like piercing when the time comes.  Trust me, someday you will want to know piercing pretty well.  It is much harder to raise weapon skill when you are at higher levels.  Also before you leave, buy your next group of spells and bank them till you need them.  This will help you stay away from halas area longer.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
