	   <tr><td colspan=2>As far a newbee weapons go, Shaman can use the best weapon lootable from a newbee zone, the cracked staff. This weapon has a better ratio than some bronze weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;My advice to any untwinked newbee shaman is to get a cracked staff and use it until lvl 10 or so and then switch to a FS Staff.  Also get a FS spear.  Use the staff for the hard fights, and the spear to rase skill.  Use the JCP for your primary weapon when you can afford one, but get a good 2HB to keep your skill up.  At higher lvl get a Runewood great staff or similar 2HB, for soloing.  You will be able to solo far better with a good ratio weapon.  <br><br>Also AC is more inportant that weapon.  Get a full set of PW and then move up to leather, from quest and looting, and then a full set of banded.  So say totemic is a waste, but if you solo it the best armor until your in your 40's<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
